              <h3 class="display-3">Privacy Policy</h3>
              <h4>1. Introduction</h4>
              <p>
                This Privacy Policy explains to Users of the Everwash Car Club
                website (<a href="https://www.everwash.com/"
                  >https://www.everwash.com/</a
                >), mobile applications offered by or powered by Everwash Car
                Club, microsites, software and service (collectively, the
                "Service"), how EverWash Car Club, LLC, doing business as
                EverWash Car Club ("EverWash", "we" or "us"), gathers and uses
                information collected in connection with use of the Service and
                the EverWash platform. Everwash takes reasonable steps to
                protect User privacy consistent with the guidelines set forth in
                this Privacy Policy and with all applicable laws. In this
                Privacy Policy, "User" or "you" means any person using the
                Service, whether by browsing the EverWash website or using
                EverWash mobile apps, paying for items and/or transactions using
                the EverWash application, engaging in loyalty and rewards
                programs ("Programs") offered by EverWash merchants (each a
                "Merchant"), or participating in any other activities available
                through the Service. <br /><br />BY ACCESSING OR USING THE
                SERVICE AND/OR THE EVERWASH PLATFORM, YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THAT YOU
                HAVE READ, UNDERSTAND, AND AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THIS PRIVACY
                POLICY AND OUR USER TERMS OF SERVICE (<a
                  href="https://www.everwash.com/terms-and-conditions"
                  >https://www.everwash.com/terms-and-conditions</a
                >). IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THESE TERMS, DO NOT USE THE SERVICE.
              </p>
              <h4>2. First Up, We Want You to Know This:</h4>
              <p>
                You control your personal information on the EverWash platform.
                We will never disclose your email address, transaction history,
                or other information to any Merchant or any other third party
                for their marketing purposes without you first authorizing that
                Merchant or third party to access such information. This allows
                you to use the EverWash Service and EverWash platform without
                receiving a whole lot of direct marketing you don't want.
              </p>
              <h4>3. Why Do We Have This Privacy Policy?</h4>
              <p>
                All companies that you do business with choose whether and how
                they want share your personal information. Federal law gives you
                the right to limit some, but not all, of that sharing. Federal
                law also requires companies to tell you how they collect, share,
                and protect your personal information. Please read this notice
                carefully to understand what we do.
              </p>
              <h4>4. What Information Do We Collect?</h4>
              <p>
                Personal Information: EverWash collects some of your identifying
                information in connection with the Service, depending on how you
                use the Service. When you create a EverWash User Account
                (whether through a EverWash App or EverWash website), pay with
                EverWash, engage in a Program, submit content to EverWash,
                complete a survey, send us feedback, request information about
                the Service, apply for a job, or sign up for special offers from
                third parties, EverWash may collect information from you, which
                could include the following (collectively, "Personal
                Information"):
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Email address</li>
                <li>Telephone number</li>
                <li>Location</li>
                <li>
                  Merchant transaction data (including the amount, date, and
                  location of the transaction, the amount of credit earned and
                  redeemed, and the identity and amount of items purchased)
                </li>
                <li>
                  Information related to your payment instruments, such as
                  expiration date and authentication codes or related
                  information.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                You do not have to provide Personal Information to EverWash, but
                you may not be able to take advantage of all features of the
                Service if you do not. <br /><br />Financial Information: In
                order to use the Service and the EverWash platform in connection
                with payments to merchants, you will need to link a payment
                instrument, such as a debit or credit card account number, to
                your EverWash User Account ("Financial Information"). EverWash
                and its providers maintain compliance with all laws and rules
                protecting the privacy of your financial information, including
                the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI-DSS).
                <br /><br />Web Tracking Information: EverWash and its
                third-party service providers may use web tracking technologies,
                such as cookies, web beacons, pixel tags and clear GIFs, to
                collect data related to usage of the Service, the Programs, and
                web and email marketing conducted by or on behalf of EverWash.
                Such data may include:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  the address of the websites you visited before and after you
                  visited the Service,
                </li>
                <li>the type of browser you are using,</li>
                <li>your Internet Protocol (IP) address, and</li>
                <li>
                  what pages in the Service you visit and what links you clicked
                  on.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                In order to collect Web Tracking Information and to make your
                use of the Service more efficient, we may store cookies on your
                computer. EverWash and third party contractors engaged to
                provide services on behalf of EverWash ("Contractors") may also
                use web tracking technologies that are placed in web pages on
                the Service or in email communications to collect information
                about actions that users take when they interact with the
                Service or such email communications. Web Tracking Information
                is not correlated by EverWash to individual users. Some Web
                Tracking Information may include data, such as IP address data,
                that is unique to you. You may be able to modify your browser
                settings to alter which web tracking technologies are permitted
                when you use the Service, but this may affect the performance of
                the Service.
              </p>
              <h4>5. How Does EverWash Use and Share Your Information?</h4>
              <p>
                All companies need to share customers' personal information to
                run their everyday business. In this section, we explain the
                reasons that companies can share their customers' personal
                information; the reasons EverWash chooses to share information;
                and whether you can limit this sharing. <br /><br />Personal
                Information: EverWash will use and store your Personal
                Information to deliver the EverWash Service to you (including
                charges, receipts, rewards tracking, and system notifications);
                to market customer rewards to you; to improve our products and
                services; to investigate (and remedy) fraudulent or allegedly
                fraudulent activity; and to perform aggregated data analysis.
                Additionally, any Personal Information that we collect via
                Facebook will be used for registration and open graph posts.
                <br /><br />EverWash does not sell or rent its mailing list, and
                we will not disclose your email address to any third party for
                marketing purposes, unless you specifically authorize a third
                party (such as an EverWash Merchant) to access your information.
                EverWash will disclose your Personal Information to third
                parties only in the following limited circumstances:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  When you use the EverWash Service at a Merchant, EverWash may
                  disclose your name (but not your email address) to the
                  associated Merchant to aid in the utilization process and
                  loyalty program tracking;
                </li>
                <li>
                  EverWash may allow our Contractors, who are performing
                  marketing services, delivering goods, administering
                  promotions, analyzing data and usage of the Service,
                  processing credit card payments, operating the Service or
                  providing support and maintenance services for the Service, or
                  providing customer service, to access Personal Information. We
                  require Contractors to use the Personal Information they
                  access only in connection with the services they perform for
                  us, and never for any marketing or other purposes.
                </li>
                <li>
                  If you are a winner of a Merchant or EverWash sponsored
                  competition (as detailed in the Applicable Contest Terms), we
                  will share your contact information for purposes of prize
                  fulfillment only.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                Financial Information: EverWash will only ever use your
                Financial Information for the purpose of submitting an
                authorized charge to your payment instrument. Financial
                Information is never provided to EverWash in unencrypted form.
                Your Financial Information is never disclosed to third parties,
                including EverWash Merchants, other than EverWash's data vault
                and payment gateway provider. <br /><br />Aggregate Information:
                EverWash may also use Personal Information to create aggregated
                data for analytical purposes. This statistical information does
                not contain any individual identifying information or contact
                information and is used to understand our customer base as a
                whole and to better serve our market. EverWash reserves the
                right to share such aggregated, non-identifiable data with 3rd
                parties. <br /><br />Web Tracking Information: EverWash uses Web
                Tracking Information to administer the Service and to understand
                how well our Service is working, and to develop aggregate,
                statistical information on usage of the Services. EverWash may
                disclose Web Tracking Information, without individual
                identifying information, to third party advertisers and
                advertising agencies, Merchants, and Contractors, in order for
                EverWash and such third parties to analyze the performance of
                the Services and the behavior of users, to operate and improve
                the Service. <br /><br />Email Communications: If you create a
                EverWash User Account and provide your email address, we will
                send you administrative and promotional emails concerning the
                EverWash Service and EverWash platform, including new features,
                promotions, Programs, and rewards. If you wish to opt out of
                promotional emails, you may do so by following the "unsubscribe"
                instructions in the email, by contacting EverWash Support, or by
                editing your EverWash User Account settings as described below.
                All EverWash Users receive administrative emails. If you wish to
                opt out of administrative emails, you must delete your account
                entirely and cease use of the Service. <br /><br />Network
                Operators: Use of the Service may involve use of the services of
                third party telecommunications carriers and service providers
                (such as the services of the carrier that provides cellphone
                service to you). Such carriers and service providers are not
                EverWash's Contractors, and any information that a carrier
                collects in connection with your use of the Service is not
                Personal Information and is not subject to this Privacy Policy.
                EverWash is not responsible for the acts or omissions of
                telecommunications carriers or service providers.
                <br /><br />Additional Disclosures: Notwithstanding anything to
                the contrary in this Privacy Policy, EverWash reserves the right
                to use or disclose Personal Information and any other
                information EverWash collects in connection with the Service:
                (a) to any successor to EverWash's business, including as a
                result of any merger, acquisition, asset sale or similar
                transaction; (b) to any law enforcement, judicial authority, or
                governmental or regulatory authority, to the extent required by
                law or legal process; or (c) if in EverWash's reasonable
                discretion, such use or disclosure is necessary to enforce or
                protect EverWash's legal rights or to protect third parties.
              </p>
              <h4>6. Privacy Settings/Opt Out</h4>
              <p>
                If you would like your Personal Information and Financial
                Information permanently removed from our database please contact
                us at
                <a href="mailto:support@everwash.com">support@everwash.com</a>
                or 1-408-686-9274 (1-408-686-WASH). We will promptly disable
                your EverWash User Account and you will no longer receive email
                from EverWash. Your removal from the mailing list or database
